				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Small problem with AoE kiting.<a name="58892"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 25 04 5:55 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Greetings.
<br />

<br />
First off, many thanks for this great web page.
<br />

<br />
Now to my problem, I have trying to figure this Ae kiting for a long time, and finaly got it right after countless deaths. Its all a matter of speed.
<br />

<br />
Well I bought a TdoK and its working great with auto circle when using Denon's ( range 35 ), however when i twist it with Chords ( range 30 ) it only land 1 of 10 trys. I tryed changing to walk mode and it helped the hitting rate alot, but still 1 of 10 dont land on a single mob, ive also tryed using a 2.4 drum mod + Selo's but i had same problem with Chords.
<br />

<br />
Now to my real consern, I've read that many bards use Selo's with TdoK and run mode and landing every chords, not all mobs but it hit every time, am I doing something wrong ? i tested this on Spirocs in tim deep, Drogmor in Gunthak, and scouts in Dulak, and had same problem every time. 
<br />

<br />
I saw a bard Ae kiting scouts in run mode + Tdok and hitting every chord + Denons.
<br />

<br />
If any could tell me what im doing wrong it would help me a great deal thanks.
<br />

<br />
Ohh yes another thing, many posts tells that RS3 is the best speed to autocircle in, I dont understand that, as when i try with regular sow the circle is to small and i get beaten down...?
<br />

<br />
Ulthar.</span></td>
