			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Small problem with AoE kiting.<a name="58911"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 25 04 9:14 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Sounds like you are using the Autocircle method, though you don't say so.
<br />

<br />
Autocircle will not be the perfect size unless you know exactly which drum to use, if any, depending on the mobs you are working with.  Too fast and you won't be landing many hits due to circle being too big.  Too slow and you get hit, stunned, and dead.
<br />

<br />
Those who you read about who land nearly 100% of the time are doing a manual circle where they watch, from a 3rd person view, many use the top down, to see how close they are to the mobs and adjust accordingly as the song is about to hit.  Rule of thumb here is that the edge of the target indicator should be just in sight for best effect.
<br />

<br />
Some here also use such things as joysticks to do their circles, instead of using the keyboard, as it can give you much better control.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, good luck and happy gaming.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
